item.title: How Do You Write cfg and class files for Rs?
item.dc:creator: @ShadowShaft ShadowShaft
item.description:
@ShadowShaft wrote:

[quote="† Java †, post:3, topic:121232"]ROFL! java files when compiled turn into bytecode wich is the text in class files… Dork!

and handlers support cfg files…[/quote]

God … your a noob … You only can use CFG files while using Tokenizer

Class file gets writing when a java file goes trough the JVM [ java virtual machine] Aka compiler
Its get formed into bytes so the java platform can read it. So it can be used on Windows , MAC , Linux

So make a file > save as > name: file.JAVA

CFG files most get readed ny the tokenizer. Tokenizer reads text of a textfile/cfg file
A Cfg file is the same! But write a file in notepad than save as> name.CFG
